WorkItem.Description:
Since a recent change, it is not possible to drop an item over another item which is a "root node".
The reason is that OnDrop do the following check : 

            // check if insertion is possible
            TreeViewExItem parentItem = item.ParentTreeViewItem;
            if (parentItem == null) return;

This test is perfectly valid for insertion, but should not be done for an actual "drop" action.

Reproduction is easy by tweaking the DragNDropSample to allow dropping on "element1"
